
Day 3 – Data Modeling

Difference Between

App
- Collection of related tabs, objects and features
- Helps users work on a specific business process
- Example: Sales App, Service App

Object
- Used to store business data in Salesforce
- Similar to a table in a database
- Contains records and fields

Record
- Single data entry inside an object
- Similar to one row in a table
- Example: One student record

Field
- Stores specific information about a record
- Similar to a column in a table
- Example: Name, Email, Age

Standard vs Custom Objects

Standard Objects
- Already provided by Salesforce
- Used for common business processes
- Examples:
  - Account
  - Contact
  - Opportunity

Custom Objects
- Created by users according to business needs
- Helps build custom applications
- Examples:
  - Student
  - Faculty
  - Course
  - Department

College Management System

Objects
- Student
- Faculty
- Course
- Department

Relationships
- One Department can contain many Faculties
- One Department can contain many Courses
- One Course can contain many Students
- Faculties can teach multiple Courses

Why Relationships are Important
- Connects related data together
- Helps avoid duplicate information
- Makes data easy to track and manage
- Improves reporting and automation

Formula Fields

Full Name
- Combines First Name and Last Name automatically
- Reduces manual work
- Maintains consistency

Remaining Seats
- Calculates available seats automatically
- Helps avoid overbooking
- Updates dynamically

Percentage
- Calculates marks percentage automatically
- Saves time for users
- Reduces calculation mistakes

Attendance Percentage
- Calculates student attendance automatically
- Helps track eligibility

Faculty Experience
- Calculates years of experience automatically

Why Formula Fields are Useful
- Eliminates repetitive calculations
- Saves time
- Reduces human errors
- Provides real-time values automatically

Validation Rules

Email cannot be empty
- Prevents missing contact details
- Ensures communication is possible

Age cannot be negative
- Prevents invalid student records
- Maintains correct data quality

Seats cannot exceed limit
- Prevents enrolling more students than capacity
- Maintains proper course management

Phone Number must contain 10 digits
- Prevents invalid phone numbers
- Improves data accuracy

Marks cannot exceed 100
- Prevents incorrect marks entry
- Ensures proper grading data

Why Validation Rules are Important
- Blocks invalid data entry
- Maintains clean database records
- Improves data consistency
- Reduces future business problems

Reflection

Why companies need structured data instead of spreadsheets
- Structured data is easier to organize
- Helps connect related information
- Improves reporting and analytics
- Supports automation and workflows
- Reduces duplicate and inconsistent data
- Provides better security and access control
- Makes large-scale business operations easier

Problems with Excel Sheets
- Difficult to manage huge data
- Higher chance of duplicate records
- No proper relationships between data
- Hard to track updates
- Difficult for multiple users to work together

Why Salesforce is Metadata-Driven
- Most customization works without coding
- Objects, fields and rules are configurable
- Businesses can change applications easily
- Faster development and maintenance
